 is necessary. Also, I'm wondering if using lowercase with underscores for the package name would be acceptable. I need to remember to include a license too, and maybe the user-code-filter should allow the test package. Let's read through that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9cKhJBpEBGfrxBmDcVprx87u|fc_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d3f37648194a8cd1fd480c45444", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-security/9.3.19.v20170502/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2562, "output": 1334, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15672, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777737001008, "responseId": "resp_05857f5c7c133a070169f61d295a808194a9e80110f8024402"}}
